Real Madrid manager, Zinedine Zidane, has named his side’s away UEFA Champions League squad that will tackle Club Brugge on Wednesday night. Zidane dropped captain, Sergio Ramos from his 19-man squad to face the Belgium side. Real Madrid made this known in a post on the club’s official website on Tuesday. The Los Blancos head to the game following a 2-0 victory over Espanyol in the La Liga last weekend. Below is Real Madrid’s squad against Club Brugge. Goalkeepers: Courtois, Areola, Altube. Defenders: Carvajal, Militão, Varane, Nacho, Odriozola, Mendy. Midfielders: Modric, Casemiro, Valverde, Isco. Forwards: Benzema, Bale, Jović, Brahim, Vinicius Jr., Rodrygo. The kick-off time for the match is 9pm. Download Daily Post App.    Subscribe to Daily Post Newsletter.    Advertise with us.   Send us enquiries, press releases.